<subSubSection id="C32165279C61865240CCFB6FFF4DFABC" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8436AC9C61865240CCFB6FFF4DFABC" blockId="19.[151,1436,946,2012]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B94FEABE9C61865240CCFB6FFEAAFB34" bold="true" box="[198,318,1186,1212]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A small to medium-sized species with asetose pronotal hypomeron, rufotestaceous legs, inconspicuously dark bluish, bluish-purplish to purplish color of head and pronotum, uniform black pubescence of abdominal tergites, and with a distinctively shaped aedoeagus and tergite 10 of female genital segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
